==Italian==

===Etymology===
From {{der|it|la|sum}} (infinitive {{m|la|esse}}), from {{inh|it|itc-pro|*ezom}}, from {{inh|it|ine-pro|*h₁ésti||I am, I exist}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈɛs.se.re/|[ˈɛs̪s̪er̺e]|lang=it}}
* {{audio|It-essere.ogg|Audio|lang=it}}
* {{rhymes|ɛssere|lang=it}}
* {{hyphenation|ès|se|re|lang=it}}

===Verb===
{{it-verb}}

# {{lb|it|intransitive|indicating existence, identity, location, or state}} to [[be]], to [[stay]]
# {{lb|it|auxiliary|the non-perfect forms followed by a past participle, used to form composite (perfect) tenses of many intransitive verbs}} to have (done something); to [[be]] in the state of having (done something); ''See [[:Category:Italian verbs taking essere as auxiliary|Category:Italian verbs taking essere as auxiliary]].''
#*{{ux|it|(io) sono<br/>(io) '''sono''' stato|I am<br/>I ('''have''') been}}
#*{{ux|it|(io) sto<br/>(io) '''sono''' stato|I stay<br/>I ('''have''') stayed}}
#*{{ux|it|accade<br/>'''è''' accaduto|it happens<br/>it ('''have''') happened}}
#*{{ux|it|(io) vado<br/>(io) '''sono''' andato|I go<br/>I ('''have''') gone}}
# {{lb|it|auxiliary|the non-perfect forms followed by a past participle, used to form composite (perfect) tenses of reflexive forms of transitive verbs}} to have (done something to oneself/oneselves); to [[be]] in the state of having (done something to oneself/oneselves); ''See [[:Category:Italian reflexive verbs|Category:Italian reflexive verbs]].''
#*{{ux|it|(io) mi ho<br/>(io) mi '''sono''' avuto|I have me/myself<br/>I ('''have''') had me/myself}}
#*{{ux|it|(io) mi faccio [...]<br/>(io) mi '''sono''' fatto [...]|I make myself [...]<br/>I ('''have''') made myself [...]}}
# {{lb|it|auxiliary|both non-perfect and perfect forms followed by a past participle, used to form the passive forms of transitive verbs}} to be (done something); to [[be]] in the state of having (done something); ''See [[:Category:Italian transitive verbs|Category:Italian transitive verbs]].''
#*{{ux|it|(io) avevo/possedevo<br/>(io) '''ero''' avuto/posseduto<br/>(io) '''ero stato''' avuto/posseduto|I owned<br/>I '''was''' possessed<br/>I '''was been''' possessed}}
#*{{ux|it|(io) amavo<br/>(io) '''ero''' amato<br/>(io) '''ero stato''' amato|I loved<br/>I '''was''' loved<br/>I '''was been''' loved}}
# {{lb|it|impersonal|of a duration of time since an event}} to have [[pass]]ed

====Usage notes====
* The present participle {{m|it|essente}} is very rare, and is usually replaced with {{m|it|stante}}, the present participle of {{m|it|stare}}. Similarly the past participle {{m|it|essuto}} has disappeared, with {{m|it|stato}}, the past participle of {{m|it|stare}}, being used instead.<ref>[http://dizionari.hoepli.it/Dizionario_Italiano/parola/essuto.aspx?idD=1&Query=essuto&lettera=E]</ref>

